  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2828",
  "title": "Add an option for control which Pit value is displayed in the RangeSlider",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nFeature.\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your use case for such a feature?**\r\n\r\nRight now we display the values at 0, 50 and 100 percent. In some cases we might want to display more / less values in the pits. We should be able to control where & when the pits are append.\r\n\r\n**Without control (current)**\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2018-03-19 at 16 30 13](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6513513/37605130-dcd09dda-2b92-11e8-8c2b-9f76cb94c208.png)\r\n\r\n**With control (wanted)**\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2018-03-19 at 16 30 22](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6513513/37605139-dfc9eac8-2b92-11e8-85a8-46661eff04f8.png)\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n\r\nRight now the generation is computed from an array `[0, 50, 100]`. Maybe we should expose this an option or a function that return an array like this one.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nLinked to https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/2755\r\n",
